original: Lindow, Anders Osvald, förste länsnotarie, Göteborg, f. 3/3/87 i Björlan-da, Gbgs o. Boh. 1. — Studiex. i Lund 06, jur. kand. där 13. Tjg. v. Norrvikens doms. 14-16, v. länsstyr. i Gbgs o. Boh. 1. sed. 16, länsnot. 20, tf. förste länsnot. 38, förste länsnot. sed. 46. RVO.
translated: Lindow, Anders Osvald, first county notary, Gothenburg, born on March 3rd, 1887 in Björlanda, Gothenburg and Bohus County. — Graduated from Lund University in 1906, received a law degree in 1913. Served at the Norrviken District Court from 1914 to 1916, deputy county administrator in Gothenburg and Bohus County from 1916. Became a county notary in 1920, acting first county notary in 1938, and first county notary from 1946 onwards. Awarded the Royal Order of Vasa (RVO).
